Package: peaceBooksR
Type: Package
Title: Peace Books Prepared For the Paris Peace Conference 
Version: 1.0
Authors@R: person(given = "Stanislav",
           family = "Pejša",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "stanislavpejsa@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5057-262X"))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <standap@gmail.com>
Description: Description: This package contains text of the Peace Books prepared by the Historical Section of the British Foreign Office and published in 1920. 
    The package contains the texts of each volumes and and then the files that
    contain all texts in in the file. 
    In the dataset peace_books_pages each line of text correspond to to a page, 
    in the dataset peace_books_volumes, each line corresponds to the content of
    the whole volume.
    The package also contains dataset peace_books_authorities that contains data 
    extracted from the list of references from each volume with the key 
    bibliographic metadata.
    The dataset peace_books_sentiment contains tokens that were matched against 
    the `Bing` sentiment dictionary. These tokens are associated with a sentiment
    value, as well as their lemmas, POS tags, and if available with the name 
    entity recognition (NER) value. 
    The corpora contains only the body of texts, section titles, footnotes, 
    running headers, tables, indices, and list of references (authorities) 
    were removed.
